# 9ja Checkr — AI handbook (read this in new chats)

## What we’re building

**Product:** Look up **NAFDAC registration numbers** → structured product JSON. Surfaces: **public web** `/verify`, **dashboard** (Google login + API keys), **HTTP API** (`x-api-key`), **Telegram bot**, **npm SDK** (`@9jacheckr/sdk`).

**No NAFDAC official API.** The server automates NAFDAC’s **public web form** (POST + session / anti-forgery), then **parses HTML** (`apps/server/src/utils/nafdacRegistrationClient.ts`, `nafdacHtmlParser.ts`). Results are **cached in MongoDB**. If NAFDAC changes HTML, update the parser.

## Monorepo

| Path | Stack | Role |
|------|--------|------|
| `apps/web` | Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, Tailwind 4 | Marketing, `/verify`, `/login`, `/dashboard/*`, BFF `POST /api/verify-lookup`, `/bot/billing/success` |
| `apps/server` | Express, MongoDB, Better Auth, Paystack | All JSON APIs under `/api/*`, webhooks |
| `apps/bot` | Telegraf | `/start`, `/verify`, `/upgrade`, `/status` → server with internal token |
| `packages/sdk` | `@9jacheckr/sdk` v0.2 | `verify`, `verifyBatch`, `searchProducts` → `https://api.9jacheckr.xyz` |

**Run:** `npm install`; `npm run dev -w web|server|bot`. **Node ≥ 20.**

## Server — middleware order (`apps/server/src/index.ts`)

1. CORS (`WEB_APP_URL`), `httpLogger`
2. Better Auth: `app.all('/api/auth/*splat', toNodeHandler(auth))`
3. **`POST /api/billing/webhook`** — **`express.raw`** only (signature); **before** `express.json`
4. `express.json`, `GET /health`
5. **`app.use('/api', requireApiAccess)`** then routers — per-mount limiters: **`/api/keys`** (high, dashboard), **`/api/bot`**, **`/api/public`** (`rateLimiter.ts`); verify + search use **`verifyPlanRateLimiter`** (see below)

**`requireApiAccess`:** Skips body for `/api/bot`, `/api/auth`, `/api/keys`, `/api/public`. Else: valid **`x-internal-bot-token`** → `req.authContext.source = 'bot'`, optional `req.botTelegram` from `x-telegram-user-*` headers (values may be URI-encoded). Else requires **`x-api-key`** → resolves user, sets `req.authContext.source = 'api_key'`, `req.apiKeyId`.

## Server — route map (all under `/api` unless noted)

| Mount | Auth | Notes |
|-------|------|--------|
| `GET /api/verify/:nafdac` | API key **or** internal bot token + Telegram headers | `verifyPlanRateLimiter`; bot quota in controller |
| `POST /api/verify/batch` | Same | **API Pro**; body `{ nafdac: string[] }` (max 40) |
| `GET /api/products/search` | Same | **API Pro**; `q`, `limit`; **`verifyPlanRateLimiter`** (same bucket as verify) |
| `POST /api/bot/activity` | `requireBotInternalToken` | |
| `POST /api/bot/status` | same | `{ telegramId }` → plan, `dailyUsed`, `dailyLimit`, `totalVerifyCount`, `periodEnd` |
| `POST /api/bot/billing/initialize-bot-pro` | same | `{ telegramId }` → Paystack URL; email `bot-tg-{id}@domain` |
| `/api/keys/*` | Per-route **`requireAuthSession`** | Keys, metrics, billing CRUD (see `apiKeyRouter.ts`) |
| `GET /api/public/verify/:nafdac` | `requireWebVerifyInternal` | Next BFF only; shared secret |

**Dashboard billing (session):** e.g. `GET/POST /api/keys/billing/...` — initialize Pro, status, account, transactions, cancel.

## Plans & limits

**API (key):** **Free** vs **API Pro** — monthly **API usage** quotas (**300** Free / **50,000** Pro, `billingConstants.ts`): verify rows (single + batch) **and** successful product searches share one counter (`MonthlyApiUsage`: `verifyCount`, `searchCount`). Per-plan rate limits, **Pro** multi-key, **metrics** (verify + search), **`POST /api/verify/batch`**, **`GET /api/products/search`**. On **Free**, only the **primary** (oldest non-revoked) key works for verify routes; other keys get **403** `KEY_PLAN_DISABLED` until Pro again. Non-primary keys also **cannot be rotated or revoked** via the dashboard API (`Revoke all` still clears every key). Services: `apiPlanService`, `monthlyApiQuotaService`, `verifyPlanRateLimiter`, `authenticateApiKeyForProductApi`.

**Bot:** **Free** = **5 lookups per UTC day** (enforced in `assertBotDailyQuotaAllows`). **Bot Pro** = no daily cap (`resolveBotPlan`). **`incrementBotDailyVerify`** increments **every** bot lookup for **telemetry** (today UTC); quota still free-only.

**`/status` (bot):** Plan + **total lookups (all time)** from `BotTelegramUserModel.verifyCount` + **today** from `BotDailyUsageModel`. Copy must **not** imply Bot Pro users are on “free tier”.

## Billing (Paystack)

- **Plans:** `PAYSTACK_PLAN_API_PRO`, `PAYSTACK_PLAN_BOT_PRO` (codes `PLN_…`, same mode as secret).
- **Webhook:** `POST /api/billing/webhook` — activates **API Pro** (metadata `userId` / tier) or **Bot Pro** (`telegramId`, `tier: bot_pro`).
- **`WEB_APP_URL`:** full origin; Paystack **`callback_url`** must be absolute (e.g. `{origin}/bot/billing/success?via=telegram` for bot).
- **Bot checkout email:** Paystack rejects fake TLDs; default domain **`9jacheckr.xyz`**, override with **`PAYSTACK_BOT_CHECKOUT_EMAIL_DOMAIN`** (real public domain).

## Mongo (high level)

Models under `apps/server/src/models/*`: products cache, users/sessions (auth), `ApiKey`, `ApiSubscription`, `MonthlyApiUsage` (`verifyCount`, `searchCount`), `BotSubscription`, `BotDailyUsage`, `BotTelegramUser` (includes `verifyCount`), payments ledger, etc. On connect: legacy **`apikeys.userId_1`** may be dropped for multi-key Pro — see `apps/server/README.md`.

## Web (`apps/web`)

- **Env:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`, **`WEB_VERIFY_INTERNAL_SECRET`** (server-only, must match API), `WEB_APP_URL`, optional server `API_BASE_URL`.
- **UI:** Reuse `SiteNav`, tokens like `text-(--text-2)`, `border-(--border)`; dashboard under `components/dashboard/`.
- **Never** expose `WEB_VERIFY_INTERNAL_SECRET` to the browser; `/api/verify-lookup` is server-side BFF.

## Bot (`apps/bot`)

- **Env:** `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `API_BASE_URL`, `BOT_INTERNAL_TOKEN`.
- **Client:** `apps/bot/src/services/apiClient.ts` — encode Telegram names for headers.
- **Public link:** `https://t.me/NaijaCheckrBot` when docs/UI reference the bot.

## SDK (`packages/sdk`)

- **`CheckrClient({ apiKey })`** only; base URL is **`DEFAULT_API_ORIGIN`** (no per-client override in code).
- Methods **resolve**; narrow on **`result.ok`**; prefer **`code`** over `message` for branching.
- **Do not** ship API keys in browser bundles.

## Stable API error `code` values

Branch on **`code`**; **`message`** may change. Include: `INVALID_NAFDAC`, `NOT_FOUND`, `MISSING_API_KEY`, `INVALID_API_KEY`, `PLAN_QUOTA_EXCEEDED`, `METRICS_NOT_AVAILABLE`, `FEATURE_REQUIRES_PRO`, `KEY_PLAN_DISABLED` (non-primary key on Free), `BOT_DAILY_LIMIT`, `KEY_LIMIT`, `RATE_LIMITED`, `INVALID_BODY`, `INVALID_QUERY`, `INTERNAL_ERROR`, etc.

## Code conventions (repo)

- **Server & bot:** TypeScript **ESM**; imports use **`.js` extension** in source.
- **API errors:** `{ ok: false, code, message }` consistent with `apps/server/src/types/types.ts`.
- **Logging:** use server `logger`; avoid silent `catch {}` except documented best-effort paths.
- **Changes:** small, task-focused diffs; match existing naming and patterns.
- **When the user expects implementation:** run commands, typecheck/build touched packages, fix failures — don’t only suggest shell steps.

## Human / prose preferences (from project owner)

- Prefer **code citations** (`startLine:endLine:path`) when pointing at existing code.
- Clear, blog-quality sentences; minimal bold; markdown links for external URLs.
- Focused diffs — no drive-by refactors.

